			%h2 Privacy Policy
			%p Our Privacy Policy explains:
			%ul
				%li What information we collect and why we collect it.
				%li How we use that information.
			
			%h4 Information we collect
			%p We collect information to provide better services to all of our users. We use cookies for the purpose of logins and authentication. Ads on this site are populated via Google Adsense and may collect some basic information from you, including but not limited to your username and your activities on The Reality League. We also use Google Analytics for monitoring traffic on this website. Google Analytics does not collect information about you, the User.

			%h4 How we use your information
			%p We use the information we collect from all of our services to provide, maintain, protect and improve them, to develop new ones, and to protect The Reality League and our users. We also use this information to offer you tailored content – like giving you more relevant search results and ads.

			%p When you contact The Reality League, we may keep a record of your communication to help solve any issues you might be facing. We may use your email address to inform you about our services, such as letting you know about upcoming changes or improvements.

			%p We use information collected from cookies and other technologies, like pixel tags, to improve your user experience and the overall quality of our services. For example, by saving your language preferences, we’ll be able to have our services appear in the language you prefer. When showing you tailored ads, we will not associate a cookie or anonymous identifier with sensitive categories, such as those based on race, religion, sexual orientation or health.

			%p We may combine personal information from one service with information, including personal information, from other Google services – for example to make it easier to share things with people you know. We will not combine DoubleClick cookie information with personally identifiable information unless we have your opt-in consent.

			%p We will ask for your consent before using information for a purpose other than those that are set out in this Privacy Policy.

			%h4 Signing in through Facebook
			%p We may use the name you provided through Facebook for your Account across all of the services we offer. If other users already have your email, or other information that identifies you, we may show them your publicly visible Profile information, such as your name and photo.